    "detail": "Very clean facility with comfortable beds and they provide towels, hair dryer, shampoo and co. Which is great! They have two separate elevators, one for male and one for female. Their is a nice lounge on top of the facility and the staff was friendly! They only thing that was annoying is that that you have to check out everyday around 10 am even if you stay several days. That means no sleeping as long as you want. However if you stay longer you can at least keep your luggage in the locker. I recommend this place if you stay only one or two days in Nagoya.",
