    "name": "Vessel Inn Sakae Station",
    "detail": "Really nice hotel for its money. Room size is typical of Japanese hotels but good enough for a couple travelling with 2 medium luggage. Nice that there is a 'pantry area' with free unlimited self-service hot and cold drinks. Breakfast buffet spread is really good and better than other dearer hotels I have stayed around Nagoya. 1 minute walk to an underpass leading to subway station which is one stop from Nagoya main station. Lost of good food options if you explore the hotel vicinity. This is the best hotel out of the 3 different hotels we've stayed in Nagoya during our trip. Will be back...",
